# The Tiny Adventure of Mochi

Once upon a sunny afternoon, a little tabby kitten named Mochi 🐾 sat by the windowsill, watching the world drift by. The curtains swayed gently, and a single golden leaf tumbled past the glass.

"Mrrrp?" Mochi tilted her head. A leaf? Indoors? Surely this called for an investigation.

She hopped down with a soft *thump*, her paws padding silently across the wooden floor. The leaf had landed near the back door, which — to her great delight — was open just a crack. 🍃

Mochi nudged the door with her tiny pink nose and slipped outside into the garden. The grass tickled her belly, the breeze ruffled her whiskers, and a butterfly fluttered by like a dancing ribbon. She chased it through the daisies, pounced on a shadow, and rolled belly-up in a warm patch of sun. ☀️

When her human finally found her, Mochi was curled in a flowerpot, purring like a tiny engine, a single petal stuck to her ear.

"There you are, troublemaker," her human laughed, scooping her up.

Mochi blinked slowly, content. The world was big, the garden was wonderful, and naps were best taken in flowerpots.

The end. 😺
